04/02/2011
WASHINGTON, United States -- Secretary of State Hillary Clinton and visiting Croatian Foreign Minister Gordan Jandrokovic signed an agreement Thursday (February 3rd) that clears the way for direct flights between their countries. The so-called Open Skies agreement is expected to boost tourism and bilateral economic ties, including "new investment opportunities", said Clinton. Jandrokovic thanked her for US support for his country and said Croatia will remain a reliable partner of NATO and trusted ally of the United States. (HRT, Nova TV, AFP - 03/02/11)
